               <head>Grant; Badley; 1384</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111653">Badley</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1384">1384</origDate>. 
                     Grant.
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename>, parson of <placeName role="parson" key="place_105562">Weston</placeName></persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Cartewaner</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105436">Needham Market</placeName>
                        </persName> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename> de <surname>Burley</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename> 
                           <surname>Dagworthe</surname>, kt.</persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> Rodynge</persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Paykyrke</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111653">Badley</placeName></persName>, all the land and tenements of Geoffrey and Henry in the town and fields of Badley, held by gift of <persName>Simon Vincent of <placeName role="person" key="place_111653">Badley</placeName></persName>, except a certain tenement called <placeName type="minor">Grettefordes</placeName>, to hold of the chief lord of the fee for the usual dues.
                     Dated: Friday after the feast of St Hilarus (14 Jan.), 7 Richard II.
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Michael</forename> 
                           <surname>Yne</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Clerk</surname></persName>, <persName>John <surname>Bateman</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Harny</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111653">Badley</placeName></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Fyshere</surname></persName>, <persName>Robert <surname>Mundeforde</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Newel</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105436">Needham Market (Needham)</placeName>
                        </persName> and many others.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
